block vars
  - var title = 'Getting Started With Swiper';

block content
  h1 Getting Started With Swiper
  h2 Installation
  p There are few options on how to include/import Swiper into your project:
  h4 a. Use Swiper from CDN
  p If you don't want to include Swiper files in your project, you may use it from CDN. The following files are available:
  ```html
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/swiper/swiper-bundle.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/swiper/swiper-bundle.min.css">

    <script src="https://unpkg.com/swiper/swiper-bundle.js"></script>
    <script src="https://unpkg.com/swiper/swiper-bundle.min.js"></script>
  ```
  p If you use ES modules in browser, there is a CDN version for that too:
  ```html
    <script type="module">
      import Swiper from 'https://unpkg.com/swiper/swiper-bundle.esm.browser.min.js'

      const swiper = new Swiper(...)
    </script>
  ```
  h4 b. Download assets
  p If you want to use Swiper assets locally, you can directly download them from <a href="https://unpkg.com/swiper/" target="_blank">https://unpkg.com/swiper/</a>
  h4 c. Install from NPM
  p We can install Swiper from NPM:
  ```
    $ npm install swiper
  ```
  ```js
    // import Swiper JS
    import Swiper from 'swiper';
    // import Swiper styles
    import 'swiper/swiper-bundle.css';

    const swiper = new Swiper(...);
  ```
  p By default Swiper exports only core version without additional modules (like Navigaion, Pagination, etc.). So you need to import and configure them too:
  ```js
    // core version + navigation, pagination modules:
    import Swiper, { Navigaion, Pagination } from 'swiper';

    // configure Swiper to use modules
    Swiper.use([Navigaion, Pagination]);

    // init Swiper:
    const swiper = new Swiper(...);
  ```
  p If you want to import Swiper with all modules (bundle) then it should be imported from `swiper/bundle`:
  ```js
    // import Swiper bundle with all modules installed
    import swiper from 'swiper/bundle';

    // init Swiper:
    const swiper = new Swiper(...);
  ```

  h3 Add Swiper HTML Layout
  p Now, we need to add basic Swiper layout to our app:
  pre
    code
      :code(lang="html")
        <!-- Slider main container -->
        <div class="swiper-container">
            <!-- Additional required wrapper -->
            <div class="swiper-wrapper">
                <!-- Slides -->
                <div class="swiper-slide">Slide 1</div>
                <div class="swiper-slide">Slide 2</div>
                <div class="swiper-slide">Slide 3</div>
                ...
            </div>
            <!-- If we need pagination -->
            <div class="swiper-pagination"></div>

            <!-- If we need navigation buttons -->
            <div class="swiper-button-prev"></div>
            <div class="swiper-button-next"></div>

            <!-- If we need scrollbar -->
            <div class="swiper-scrollbar"></div>
        </div>
  h3 Swiper CSS Styles/Size
  p In addition to <a href="/api/#styles" target="_blank">Swiper's CSS styles</a>, we may need to add some custom styles to set Swiper size:
  ```css
    .swiper-container {
        width: 600px;
        height: 300px;
    }
  ```

  h3 Initialize Swiper
  p Finally, we need to initialize Swiper in JS:
  pre(style="width:100%")
    code.js
      :code(lang="js")
        var mySwiper = new Swiper('.swiper-container', {
          // Optional parameters
          direction: 'vertical',
          loop: true,

          // If we need pagination
          pagination: {
            el: '.swiper-pagination',
          },

          // Navigation arrows
          navigation: {
            nextEl: '.swiper-button-next',
            prevEl: '.swiper-button-prev',
          },

          // And if we need scrollbar
          scrollbar: {
            el: '.swiper-scrollbar',
          },
        })

  h2 What next?
  p As you see it is really easy to integrate Swiper into your website or app. So here are your next steps:
  ul
    li Go to <a href="../api/">API Documentation</a> to learn more about all Swiper API and how to control it.
    li Look at available <a href="../demos/" target="_blank">Demos</a>.
    li If you have questions about Swiper ask them in <a href="http://stackoverflow.com" target="_blank">StackOverflow</a> and don't forget to tag your question with <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/swiper" target="_blank"><code>swiper</code></a> tag.
    li Create issue on <a href="https://github.com/nolimits4web/swiper/" target="_blank">GitHub</a> if you found a bug.
